{
  "doc_id": "9630",
  "text": "In this work we are concerned with maximality considerations under intransitivity of the indifference. It is based on the analysis of \"undominated maximals\", a concept introduced and explored in Peris and Subiza [CITATION_1] . They establish two particularly remarkable facts. For one thing, such selection of maximals can be done when the set of alternatives is finite provided that the binary relation is acyclic. For another, proceeding in this way is the same as using Luce's selected maximals 2 in the case of semiorders.",
  "correct_citation": {
